WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
Oxford Bookworms Stage 1. The Adventures of Tom Sawyer by Mark Twain. Retold by Nick

00:10.000 --> 00:20.000
Bollard. Read by William DeFries. Published and copyright, Oxford University Press 1997.

00:41.000 --> 00:46.000
Chapter 1. Tom and his friends.

00:49.000 --> 00:55.000
Tom! Tom! Where are you?

00:57.000 --> 00:59.000
No answer.

01:00.000 --> 01:06.000
Where is that boy? When I find him, I'm going to.

01:07.000 --> 01:16.000
And Polly looked under the bed. Then she opened the door and looked out into the garden.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
Tom!

01:20.000 --> 01:31.000
She heard something behind her. A small boy ran past, but Ann Polly put out her hand and stopped him.

01:32.000 --> 01:38.000
Ah, there you are. And what's that in your pocket?

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
Nothing, Ann Polly.

01:43.000 --> 01:48.000
Nothing. It's an apple. I can see it.

01:49.000 --> 01:55.000
Now listen, Tom. Those apples are not for you. And I.

01:56.000 --> 02:02.000
Oh, Ann Polly! Quick! Look behind you!

02:04.000 --> 02:14.000
So Ann Polly looked. And Tom was out of the house in a second. She laughed quietly.

02:15.000 --> 02:24.000
Oh, I never learned. I love that, Tom. My dead sister's child.

02:26.000 --> 02:37.000
But he isn't an easy boy for an old lady. Well, it's Saturday tomorrow and there's no school.

02:38.000 --> 02:49.000
But it isn't going to be a holiday for Tom. Oh, no. He's going to work tomorrow.

02:50.000 --> 03:05.000
Saturday was a beautiful day. It was summer and the sun was hot. And there were flowers in all the gardens.

03:06.000 --> 03:11.000
It was a day for everybody to be happy.

03:12.000 --> 03:21.000
Tom came out of his house with a brush and a big pot of white paint in his hand.

03:22.000 --> 03:31.000
He looked at the fence. It was three meters high and 30 meters long.

03:32.000 --> 03:38.000
He put his brush in the paint and painted some of the fence.

03:39.000 --> 03:46.000
He did it again. Then he stopped and looked at the fence.

03:47.000 --> 03:51.000
Put down his brush and sat down.

03:52.000 --> 04:02.000
There were hours of work in front of him. And he was the unhappiest boy in the village.

04:03.000 --> 04:13.000
After 10 minutes, Tom had an idea. A wonderful idea.

04:14.000 --> 04:19.000
He took up the brush again and began work.

04:20.000 --> 04:28.000
He saw his friend, Joe Harper, in the street. But he didn't look at him.

04:29.000 --> 04:37.000
Joe had an apple in his hand. He came up to Tom and looked at the fence.

04:38.000 --> 04:49.000
I am sorry, Tom. Tom said nothing. The paintbrush moved up and down.

04:50.000 --> 04:57.000
Working for your aunt, said Joe. I am going down to the river.

04:58.000 --> 05:02.000
I am sorry, you can't come with me.

05:03.000 --> 05:06.000
Tom put down his brush.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
You call this work? He said.

05:11.000 --> 05:15.000
Painting a fence, said Joe.

05:16.000 --> 05:19.000
Of course it's work.

05:20.000 --> 05:25.000
Perhaps it is. And perhaps it isn't.

05:26.000 --> 05:29.000
But I like it, said Tom.

05:31.000 --> 05:38.000
I can go to the river any day. I can't paint a fence very often.

05:39.000 --> 05:49.000
Joe watched Tom for about five minutes. Tom painted very slowly and carefully.

05:50.000 --> 05:58.000
He often stopped, moved back from the fence, and looked at his work with a smile.

05:59.000 --> 06:08.000
Joe began to get very interested and said, Tom, can I paint a little?

06:09.000 --> 06:12.000
Tom thought for a second.

06:13.000 --> 06:21.000
I am sorry, Joe. You see, my aunt wants me to do it because I am good at painting.

06:22.000 --> 06:28.000
My brother said wanted to paint too, but she said no.

06:29.000 --> 06:36.000
Oh, please, Tom. Just a little. I am good at painting too.

06:37.000 --> 06:41.000
Hey, do you want some of my apple?

06:42.000 --> 06:45.000
No, Joe. I can't.

06:46.000 --> 06:51.000
Okay, you can have all my apple.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.000
Tom gave Joe the brush.

06:56.000 --> 07:05.000
He did not smile, but for the first time that day, he was a very happy boy.

07:06.000 --> 07:10.000
He sat down and ate Joe's apple.

07:11.000 --> 07:20.000
More friends came to laugh at Tom, but soon they all wanted to paint too.

07:21.000 --> 07:33.000
By the afternoon, Tom had three balls, an old knife, a cat with one eye, an old blue bottle,

07:34.000 --> 07:38.000
and a lot of other exciting things.

07:39.000 --> 07:44.000
He was the richest boy in St. Petersburg.

07:45.000 --> 07:53.000
And the fence, all 30 meters of it, was a beautiful white.

07:54.000 --> 07:57.000
He went back to the house.

07:58.000 --> 08:03.000
And Polly, can I go and play now?

08:04.000 --> 08:08.000
And Polly came out of the house to look.

08:09.000 --> 08:16.000
When she saw the beautiful white fence, she was very pleased.

08:17.000 --> 08:22.000
She took Tom into the house and gave him an apple.

08:23.000 --> 08:29.000
Well, you can go and play, but don't come home late!

08:31.000 --> 08:36.000
Tom quickly took a second apple and ran off.

08:39.000 --> 08:51.000
On Monday morning, Tom didn't want to go to school, but Aunt Polly got him out of bed, and then out of the house.

08:53.000 --> 08:59.000
In the street near the school, he met his friend, Huckleberry Finn.

09:00.000 --> 09:06.000
Hock had no mother, and his father drank whiskey all the time.

09:07.000 --> 09:10.000
So Hock lived in the streets.

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
He didn't go to school.

09:14.000 --> 09:19.000
He was always dirty, and he never had a new shirt.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
But he was happy.

09:23.000 --> 09:31.000
The mothers of St. Petersburg didn't like Hock, but Tom and his friends did.

09:33.000 --> 09:34.000
Hello, Hock!

09:35.000 --> 09:36.000
Said Tom.

09:37.000 --> 09:38.000
What have you got there?

09:40.000 --> 09:41.000
A dead cat.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.000
What are you gonna do with it?

09:45.000 --> 09:46.000
Ask Tom.

09:48.000 --> 09:53.000
I'm gonna take it to the graveyard tonight, Hock said.

09:54.000 --> 10:03.000
At midnight, a dead cat can call ghosts out of their graves.

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
I never heard that!

10:08.000 --> 10:09.000
Said Tom.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.000
Is it true?

10:12.000 --> 10:16.000
Well, I don't know, said Hock.

10:17.000 --> 10:20.000
Old Mrs. Hockkins told me.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.000
Come with me and see.

10:24.000 --> 10:28.000
Or are you afraid of ghosts?

10:30.000 --> 10:31.000
Of course not!

10:32.000 --> 10:33.000
Said Tom.

10:34.000 --> 10:38.000
Come in me out for me at my window at eleven o'clock.

10:42.000 --> 10:45.000
After this, Tom was late for school.

10:46.000 --> 10:49.000
And the teacher looked at him angrily.

10:51.000 --> 10:55.000
Tom is Sawyer. Why are you late again?

10:56.000 --> 10:57.000
He said.

10:58.000 --> 11:00.000
Tom began to speak.

11:01.000 --> 11:03.000
And then stopped.

11:05.000 --> 11:08.000
There was a new girl in the school room.

11:09.000 --> 11:16.000
A beautiful girl with blue eyes and long yellow hair.

11:18.000 --> 11:21.000
Tom looked and looked.

11:24.000 --> 11:27.000
Oh, how beautiful she was.

11:29.000 --> 11:34.000
And in two seconds, Tom was in love.

11:35.000 --> 11:37.000
He must sit next to her.

11:39.000 --> 11:40.000
But how?

11:42.000 --> 11:46.000
In the girl's half of the room, there was only one empty chair.

11:47.000 --> 11:50.000
And it was next to the new girl.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.000
Tom thought quickly.

11:54.000 --> 11:56.000
And then looked at the teacher.

11:58.000 --> 12:01.000
I stopped to talk with Hocko Berry Finn.

12:02.000 --> 12:03.000
He said.

12:04.000 --> 12:08.000
The teacher was very, very angry.

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
Boys were often late for school.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.000
That was bad.

12:16.000 --> 12:20.000
But talking with Hocko Berry Finn was worse.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
Much worse.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
The teacher took his stick.

12:28.000 --> 12:30.000
And two minutes later,

12:31.000 --> 12:34.000
Tom's trousers were very hot.

12:35.000 --> 12:39.000
And the teacher's arm was very tired.

12:41.000 --> 12:47.000
Now, Tom Sawyer, you go and sit with the girls.

12:49.000 --> 12:51.000
Some of the children laughed.

12:53.000 --> 12:57.000
Tom walked to the chair next to the new girl.

12:58.000 --> 13:01.000
Sat down and opened his book.

13:03.000 --> 13:06.000
The other children began to work again.

13:08.000 --> 13:12.000
After ten minutes, the girl looked up.

13:14.000 --> 13:17.000
There was an apple on the table in front of her.

13:19.000 --> 13:22.000
She put it back on Tom's half of the table.

13:23.000 --> 13:27.000
A minute later, the apple was in front of her again.

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
Now, it stayed.

13:35.000 --> 13:40.000
Next, Tom drew a picture of a house and put it in front of her.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
That's nice.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.000
The girl said.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.000
Now draw a man.

13:53.000 --> 13:57.000
Tom drew a man next to the house.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.000
The man was taller than the house.

14:02.000 --> 14:08.000
And he had very big hands and very long legs.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.000
But the girl liked him.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.000
Can you draw me now?

14:17.000 --> 14:19.000
She asked.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.000
Tom drew a girl next to the man.

14:26.000 --> 14:29.000
You draw beautifully.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.000
I can't draw pictures.

14:34.000 --> 14:39.000
I can teach you, said Tom, after school.

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
Oh, please.

14:43.000 --> 14:45.000
What's your name?

14:46.000 --> 14:47.000
Tom asked.

14:48.000 --> 14:52.000
Becky? Becky Thatcher?

14:53.000 --> 14:58.000
Just then, Tom felt a hand on his head.

14:59.000 --> 15:01.000
It was the teacher.

15:02.000 --> 15:08.000
He took Tom by the ear and moved him back to his chair.

15:09.000 --> 15:12.000
In the boy's half of the room.

15:17.000 --> 15:19.000
Chapter 2

15:20.000 --> 15:22.000
In the graveyard.

15:25.000 --> 15:31.000
That night, Tom went to bed at half past nine.

15:32.000 --> 15:35.000
He waited for Hux Miao.

15:36.000 --> 15:39.000
And at eleven o'clock, it came.

15:41.000 --> 15:45.000
He climbed quietly out of the bedroom window.

15:46.000 --> 15:52.000
And then he and Hux walked out of the village with the dead cat.

15:54.000 --> 16:00.000
The graveyard was on a hill, about a mile from St. Petersburg.

16:01.000 --> 16:07.000
When the boys got there, they put the dead cat on a grave

16:08.000 --> 16:11.000
and sat down behind some trees.

16:12.000 --> 16:16.000
They watched and waited.

16:17.000 --> 16:23.000
It was very dark and very quiet.

16:24.000 --> 16:29.000
Do you see that new grave there?

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
whispered Hux.

16:33.000 --> 16:36.000
That's Hux William's grave.

16:37.000 --> 16:39.000
He died last week.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.000
Perhaps he can hear us.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
Tom whispered back.

16:47.000 --> 16:49.000
Do you think he can, Hux?

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
I don't know.

16:52.000 --> 16:54.000
But I...

16:55.000 --> 16:56.000
Oh, Tom.

16:57.000 --> 16:58.000
What is it?

16:58.000 --> 16:59.000
Shh!

17:00.000 --> 17:01.000
Whispered Tom.

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
I can see something.

17:05.000 --> 17:06.000
Look!

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
Hux moved near to Tom.

17:13.000 --> 17:14.000
Gross!

17:15.000 --> 17:16.000
He said.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.000
Three of them.

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
They're coming here, Tom.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.000
Oh, let's go home.

17:27.000 --> 17:29.000
They can't see us.

17:30.000 --> 17:31.000
Tom whispered.

17:32.000 --> 17:33.000
Not here.

17:35.000 --> 17:38.000
Ghost can see through trees.

17:39.000 --> 17:41.000
Said Hux unhappily.

17:42.000 --> 17:46.000
They can see through everything.

17:49.000 --> 17:54.000
The ghosts moved quietly through the graveyard

17:55.000 --> 17:58.000
and came near to the trees.

18:00.000 --> 18:03.000
Hux and Tom watched.

18:04.000 --> 18:06.000
Very afraid.

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
Then, after a minute,

18:11.000 --> 18:12.000
Hux said.

18:14.000 --> 18:17.000
Tom, they're not ghosts.

18:18.000 --> 18:20.000
That's Muff Potter.

18:22.000 --> 18:24.000
So it is.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.000
And that's engine Joe.

18:29.000 --> 18:33.000
And the other man is Dr. Robinson.

18:35.000 --> 18:37.000
What do they do in here?

18:38.000 --> 18:41.000
They're grave robbers, Tom.

18:42.000 --> 18:45.000
They're going to rob a grave.

18:46.000 --> 18:49.000
My father told me about it.

18:50.000 --> 18:54.000
The doctor wants a dead body, you see.

18:55.000 --> 19:00.000
He cuts it up because he wants to learn about...

19:01.000 --> 19:02.000
Shh!

19:03.000 --> 19:04.000
Said Tom.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.000
They're getting near.

19:10.000 --> 19:14.000
The three men stopped at Haas-Williams grave.

19:15.000 --> 19:20.000
And engine Joe and Muff Potter began to dig.

19:22.000 --> 19:26.000
Ten minutes later, the grave was open.

19:28.000 --> 19:32.000
Now, Dr. said Muff Potter.

19:33.000 --> 19:38.000
You want us to take the body to your house?

19:39.000 --> 19:42.000
That's five dollars more.

19:44.000 --> 19:45.000
No.

19:46.000 --> 19:47.000
Said the doctor.

19:48.000 --> 19:51.000
I gave you the money this morning.

19:52.000 --> 19:55.000
I'm not giving you any more.

19:57.000 --> 20:01.000
Now you listen to me, Dr.

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
said engine Joe.

20:05.000 --> 20:08.000
I want that money.

20:09.000 --> 20:13.000
Do you remember a day five years ago?

20:14.000 --> 20:20.000
I came to your house and asked for something to eat.

20:21.000 --> 20:24.000
And you gave me nothing.

20:25.000 --> 20:26.000
Nothing.

20:27.000 --> 20:30.000
So give me that money.

20:32.000 --> 20:34.000
He took the doctor's arm.

20:35.000 --> 20:38.000
But suddenly, the doctor hit him.

20:39.000 --> 20:42.000
And engine Joe fell to the ground.

20:45.000 --> 20:47.000
Don't hit my friend!

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
Cried Muff Potter.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.000
He jumped on the doctor.

20:54.000 --> 20:57.000
And the two men began to fight.

20:58.000 --> 21:01.000
It all happened very quickly.

21:02.000 --> 21:07.000
And the two boys watched with open mouths.

21:09.000 --> 21:11.000
Engine Joe got up.

21:12.000 --> 21:16.000
He had Muff Potter's knife in his hand now.

21:17.000 --> 21:20.000
And he moved behind the doctor.

21:21.000 --> 21:25.000
Then the doctor hit Muff Potter on the head.

21:26.000 --> 21:29.000
Muff fell to the ground.

21:30.000 --> 21:39.000
And at the same moment, the knife in engine Joe's hand went into the doctor's back.

21:40.000 --> 21:45.000
The doctor fell to the ground on top of Muff Potter.

21:46.000 --> 21:49.000
And he did not move again.

21:50.000 --> 21:54.000
The two boys could watch no more.

21:55.000 --> 21:57.000
Very quietly.

21:58.000 --> 22:01.000
They moved away from the trees.

22:02.000 --> 22:05.000
And then ran out of the graveyard.

22:06.000 --> 22:08.000
And back to the village.

22:11.000 --> 22:15.000
Engine Joe stood by Haas Williams' grave.

22:16.000 --> 22:19.000
And looked down at the two men.

22:21.000 --> 22:28.000
Then he put the knife into Muff Potter's hand and sat down.

22:29.000 --> 22:37.000
Three, four, five minutes went by.

22:38.000 --> 22:43.000
Potter moved a little and opened his eyes.

22:44.000 --> 22:46.000
What?

22:47.000 --> 22:49.000
What happened, Joe?

22:50.000 --> 22:52.000
He asked.

22:53.000 --> 22:57.000
This is bad, Muff, said Joe.

22:58.000 --> 23:01.000
Why did you kill him?

23:02.000 --> 23:06.000
Muff looked at the doctor's dead body.

23:06.000 --> 23:10.000
Then at the knife in his hand.

23:11.000 --> 23:12.000
Me?

23:13.000 --> 23:15.000
Did I kill him?

23:16.000 --> 23:19.000
His face went white.

23:20.000 --> 23:24.000
And the knife fell from his hand.

23:25.000 --> 23:28.000
It's the whiskey, Joe.

23:29.000 --> 23:32.000
I never fight with knives.

23:33.000 --> 23:36.000
I never fight with knives, usually.

23:38.000 --> 23:44.000
Oh, why did I drink all that whiskey tonight?

23:46.000 --> 23:49.000
I don't remember anything.

23:52.000 --> 23:54.000
It's okay, Muff.

23:55.000 --> 23:56.000
Said Joe.

23:57.000 --> 23:59.000
I'm not going to tell anyone.

24:00.000 --> 24:02.000
You get away quickly.

24:04.000 --> 24:05.000
Go on.

24:06.000 --> 24:07.000
Go now.

24:10.000 --> 24:14.000
Muff Potter got up and ran away.

24:16.000 --> 24:18.000
Joe watched him for a minute.

24:19.000 --> 24:24.000
Then he carefully put the knife next to the doctor's body.

24:25.000 --> 24:29.000
Then he, too, left the graveyard.

24:34.000 --> 24:41.000
The next day, the sheriff's men found the doctor's body in the graveyard.

24:42.000 --> 24:45.000
And Muff Potter's knife.

24:47.000 --> 24:52.000
That night, Muff came to the graveyard to get his knife.

24:53.000 --> 24:56.000
But the sheriff's men were there.

24:57.000 --> 25:01.000
And they took Muff to St. Petersburg's little jail.

25:03.000 --> 25:10.000
And there Muff sat for four weeks and waited for his trial.

25:15.000 --> 25:19.000
Tom and Huck could not forget that night in the graveyard.

25:22.000 --> 25:28.000
They were very unhappy and very afraid.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.000
What are we going to do?

25:33.000 --> 25:34.000
Said Tom.

25:35.000 --> 25:38.000
Muff Potter didn't kill the doctor.

25:39.000 --> 25:40.000
Engine Joe did.

25:41.000 --> 25:43.000
We saw him.

25:44.000 --> 25:47.000
I know, Huck said.

25:49.000 --> 25:51.000
But what can we do?

25:53.000 --> 25:55.000
We can't tell anyone.

25:57.000 --> 25:59.000
I'm afraid of engine Joe.

26:01.000 --> 26:02.000
He's dangerous.

26:04.000 --> 26:05.000
And he's a killer.

26:07.000 --> 26:09.000
Do you want a knife in your back?

26:12.000 --> 26:15.000
Yes. I'm afraid of him, too.

26:16.000 --> 26:17.000
Tom said.

26:19.000 --> 26:20.000
He thought for a minute.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.000
I'm sorry for Muff Potter.

26:26.000 --> 26:28.000
But you're right, Huck.

26:29.000 --> 26:33.000
We can't tell anyone about engine Joe.

26:40.000 --> 26:41.000
Chapter 3

26:43.000 --> 26:45.000
On Jackson's Island.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.000
The summer holidays came.

26:50.000 --> 26:53.000
And there was no school.

26:54.000 --> 26:59.000
Tom didn't want to think about Muff Potter and engine Joe.

27:00.000 --> 27:02.000
But it wasn't easy.

27:03.000 --> 27:06.000
At night, when he was in bed,

27:07.000 --> 27:11.000
he saw engine Joe's face in the dark.

27:12.000 --> 27:14.000
And he couldn't sleep.

27:15.000 --> 27:18.000
But he couldn't talk to anyone about it.

27:21.000 --> 27:23.000
One hot summer's day,

27:24.000 --> 27:28.000
he and Joe Harper were down by the Mississippi River.

27:29.000 --> 27:32.000
They sat and watched the boats,

27:33.000 --> 27:35.000
and fished and talked.

27:37.000 --> 27:39.000
Let's get away from here.

27:40.000 --> 27:42.000
Said Tom, suddenly.

27:43.000 --> 27:46.000
Let's go and do something exciting somewhere.

27:47.000 --> 27:48.000
Okay.

27:49.000 --> 27:50.000
Said Joe.

27:51.000 --> 27:52.000
But what?

27:53.000 --> 27:54.000
And where?

27:55.000 --> 27:56.000
I know.

27:57.000 --> 27:58.000
Tom said.

27:59.000 --> 28:00.000
Let's run away.

28:01.000 --> 28:04.000
Let's go and live on Jackson's Island.

28:05.000 --> 28:08.000
We can sleep out under the trees.

28:11.000 --> 28:14.000
Jackson's Island was in the Mississippi.

28:15.000 --> 28:18.000
Three miles south of St. Petersburg.

28:19.000 --> 28:21.000
Nobody lived there.

28:23.000 --> 28:25.000
Let's ask Huck Finn too.

28:26.000 --> 28:27.000
Said Tom.

28:28.000 --> 28:32.000
But don't tell your mother or father or anyone.

28:33.000 --> 28:36.000
Go home and get some things to eat.

28:37.000 --> 28:39.000
And meet me here at midnight.

28:40.000 --> 28:46.000
So that night, three boys in a small boat

28:47.000 --> 28:50.000
went down the river to Jackson's Island.

28:52.000 --> 28:55.000
They had some bread and some meat.

28:56.000 --> 28:58.000
And Huck had his pipe too.

29:00.000 --> 29:02.000
When they got there,

29:03.000 --> 29:05.000
they carried everything on to the island

29:06.000 --> 29:07.000
and made a fire.

29:08.000 --> 29:10.000
Under a big old tree.

29:12.000 --> 29:15.000
Then they cooked some of the meat over the fire.

29:16.000 --> 29:21.000
And oh, that meat was good.

29:22.000 --> 29:25.000
The best dinner in the world.

29:27.000 --> 29:30.000
Soon, they stopped talking.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.000
Their eyes closed.

29:34.000 --> 29:36.000
And they slept.

29:38.000 --> 29:43.000
The next morning, Tom woke up with the sun on his head

29:44.000 --> 29:47.000
and a smile on his face.

29:49.000 --> 29:51.000
Then Huck and Joe woke up.

29:52.000 --> 29:56.000
And the three boys ran down to the river to swim.

29:58.000 --> 30:00.000
After that, they fished.

30:02.000 --> 30:06.000
And soon they had about six big fish for their breakfast.

30:08.000 --> 30:12.000
They cooked the fish on their fire and ate them all.

30:14.000 --> 30:16.000
They were very hungry.

30:18.000 --> 30:24.000
That, said Joe happily, was a wonderful breakfast.

30:28.000 --> 30:31.000
After breakfast, they walked through the island.

30:32.000 --> 30:38.000
Swam some more, talked, fished and swam again.

30:40.000 --> 30:43.000
They came back to their fire in the afternoon.

30:45.000 --> 30:48.000
Suddenly, Tom looked up and said,

30:50.000 --> 30:53.000
Listen, can you hear boats?

30:56.000 --> 31:00.000
They listened and then ran across the island.

31:01.000 --> 31:03.000
To look down the river.

31:04.000 --> 31:08.000
There were twenty or more boats on the water.

31:09.000 --> 31:12.000
Every boat in St. Petersburg was out.

31:14.000 --> 31:16.000
What are they doing?

31:17.000 --> 31:18.000
Ask Joe.

31:20.000 --> 31:23.000
They're looking for a dead body, I think.

31:24.000 --> 31:25.000
Said Huck.

31:26.000 --> 31:28.000
They did that last summer.

31:29.000 --> 31:32.000
When Bill Turner fell in the river and drowned.

31:34.000 --> 31:36.000
Who's dead, do you think?

31:37.000 --> 31:38.000
Ask Joe.

31:40.000 --> 31:42.000
The boys watched the boats.

31:44.000 --> 31:46.000
Suddenly, Tom cried.

31:47.000 --> 31:48.000
I know who's dead.

31:49.000 --> 31:50.000
It's us.

31:51.000 --> 31:53.000
They're looking for us.

31:54.000 --> 31:57.000
This was wonderful.

31:58.000 --> 32:01.000
Tom looked at his friends.

32:02.000 --> 32:06.000
We're famous, he said.

32:07.000 --> 32:11.000
Everybody in St. Petersburg is talking about us.

32:13.000 --> 32:16.000
And they all feel sorry for us.

32:19.000 --> 32:20.000
Night came.

32:21.000 --> 32:23.000
And the boys went to sleep.

32:25.000 --> 32:27.000
But Tom did not sleep.

32:29.000 --> 32:33.000
And when morning came, he wasn't there.

32:35.000 --> 32:36.000
Huck.

32:37.000 --> 32:38.000
Where's Tom?

32:39.000 --> 32:40.000
Cried Joe.

32:42.000 --> 32:43.000
I don't know.

32:44.000 --> 32:45.000
Huck began.

32:46.000 --> 32:48.000
But, look.

32:48.000 --> 32:49.000
Look.

32:50.000 --> 32:51.000
There he is.

32:52.000 --> 32:55.000
He's swimming across to the island now.

32:57.000 --> 32:58.000
Hey, Tom!

33:02.000 --> 33:06.000
At breakfast, Tom told his story.

33:08.000 --> 33:11.000
I went home last night, he said.

33:12.000 --> 33:14.000
And listened at the window.

33:15.000 --> 33:18.000
Joe, your mother was there too.

33:19.000 --> 33:23.000
And she and Aunt Polly cried and cried.

33:26.000 --> 33:28.000
I heard some very interesting things.

33:31.000 --> 33:37.000
On Sunday, there's going to be a big funeral at the church.

33:38.000 --> 33:39.000
For us.

33:40.000 --> 33:45.000
And listen, I've got a wonderful idea.

33:47.000 --> 33:51.000
Huck and Joe listened and laughed.

33:52.000 --> 33:58.000
And yes, it was a wonderful idea.

34:02.000 --> 34:06.000
That night, the boys cooked some more fish.

34:07.000 --> 34:13.000
And after dinner, Huck got out his pipe and began to smoke.

34:15.000 --> 34:16.000
Can we smoke too?

34:17.000 --> 34:18.000
Asked Tom.

34:19.000 --> 34:20.000
I want to learn.

34:22.000 --> 34:25.000
So Huck made pipes for Tom and Joe.

34:26.000 --> 34:29.000
And the three boys sat and smoked.

34:30.000 --> 34:32.000
Hey, I like smoking.

34:33.000 --> 34:34.000
Said Tom.

34:35.000 --> 34:36.000
It's easy.

34:38.000 --> 34:39.000
It's nothing.

34:40.000 --> 34:41.000
Said Joe.

34:42.000 --> 34:45.000
I'm going to smoke every day.

34:46.000 --> 34:55.000
But after ten minutes, Tom and Joe got quieter and quieter.

34:56.000 --> 35:00.000
And their faces went an interesting color.

35:02.000 --> 35:05.000
I'm going for a little walk now.

35:06.000 --> 35:07.000
Said Tom.

35:08.000 --> 35:14.000
He stood up carefully and walked away into the trees.

35:15.000 --> 35:16.000
Mato.

35:17.000 --> 35:18.000
Said Joe.

35:19.000 --> 35:20.000
Quickly.

35:21.000 --> 35:26.000
The two boys came back an hour later.

35:27.000 --> 35:32.000
But they didn't smoke their pipes again.

35:33.000 --> 35:39.000
On Sunday morning, there were no happy faces in St. Petersburg.

35:40.000 --> 35:47.000
And Polly and Joe's mother and father were in the church and all the boys' friends.

35:48.000 --> 35:54.000
The minister said some very nice things about the three boys.

35:55.000 --> 36:00.000
And the boys' families cried and cried.

36:01.000 --> 36:02.000
Everybody cried.

36:04.000 --> 36:10.000
And little Becky Thatcher did not stop crying for one second.

36:12.000 --> 36:16.000
There was a small noise at the back of the church.

36:18.000 --> 36:21.000
But at first, nobody heard it.

36:22.000 --> 36:28.000
Then the minister looked up and suddenly stopped speaking.

36:29.000 --> 36:32.000
Everybody turned to look.

36:33.000 --> 36:38.000
Their mouths opened and stayed open.

36:40.000 --> 36:45.000
And into the church came the three dead boys.

36:46.000 --> 36:51.000
Tom first, Joe next, and then Huck.

36:54.000 --> 36:58.000
For a second, nobody moved or spoke.

37:00.000 --> 37:02.000
And then the noise began.

37:04.000 --> 37:10.000
Aunt Polly and Joe's mother ran to the boys and took them in their arms.

37:11.000 --> 37:16.000
Aunt Polly cried and laughed and cried again.

37:18.000 --> 37:19.000
Oh, Tom?

37:20.000 --> 37:26.000
She said, you're a bad boy, but I love you.

37:29.000 --> 37:31.000
Suddenly the minister called out.

37:33.000 --> 37:36.000
All happy days.

37:37.000 --> 37:42.000
Sing good people of St. Petersburg.

37:43.000 --> 37:47.000
Sing and be happy.

37:50.000 --> 37:58.000
And everybody sang and smiled and laughed for a long time.

38:00.000 --> 38:04.000
It was St. Petersburg's happiest funeral.

38:07.000 --> 38:13.000
The weeks went by and the judge came to St. Petersburg.

38:14.000 --> 38:22.000
On the day before Muff Potter's trial, Huck and Tom met in the street near Tom's house.

38:23.000 --> 38:26.000
Huck was unhappy.

38:27.000 --> 38:34.000
Tom, you didn't tell anyone about, you know.

38:35.000 --> 38:36.000
No, I didn't.

38:37.000 --> 38:40.000
But Huck, what about Muff?

38:41.000 --> 38:44.000
People are saying he's the killer.

38:45.000 --> 38:47.000
And he's going to die.

38:49.000 --> 38:56.000
But we can't tell anyone about engine Joe, said Huck.

38:57.000 --> 38:59.000
I don't want to die, too.

39:00.000 --> 39:01.000
Do you?

39:04.000 --> 39:05.000
No.

39:06.000 --> 39:08.000
Tom didn't want to die.

39:09.000 --> 39:14.000
But he couldn't forget Muff Potter's face in the jail.

39:15.000 --> 39:20.000
Old, tired and unhappy.

39:22.000 --> 39:25.000
And engine Joe was a free man.

39:27.000 --> 39:29.000
It wasn't right.

39:30.000 --> 39:37.000
That night, Tom came home late and very excited.

39:38.000 --> 39:42.000
He could not sleep for two or three hours.

39:45.000 --> 39:50.000
The next morning, all the village was at Muff Potter's trial.

39:52.000 --> 39:54.000
Engine Joe was there, too.

39:56.000 --> 39:58.000
Muff waited.

39:59.000 --> 40:04.000
A tired old man with a dirty face.

40:05.000 --> 40:08.000
The judge began the trial.

40:10.000 --> 40:14.000
Questions, questions, questions.

40:15.000 --> 40:19.000
Answers, answers, answers.

40:20.000 --> 40:25.000
And the answers were all bad for Muff Potter.

40:26.000 --> 40:34.000
Yes, I found the knife in the graveyard next to Dr. Robinson's body.

40:36.000 --> 40:42.000
Yes, that's Muff Potter's knife. He always carries it.

40:45.000 --> 40:50.000
Yes, I saw Muff Potter in the village that afternoon.

40:51.000 --> 40:55.000
He had the knife with him then.

40:57.000 --> 41:02.000
Muff Potter began to look more and more unhappy.

41:04.000 --> 41:06.000
Then the judge said,

41:07.000 --> 41:10.000
Call Thomas Sawyer.

41:12.000 --> 41:15.000
St. Petersburg sat up.

41:16.000 --> 41:19.000
What did young Tom Sawyer know?

41:21.000 --> 41:26.000
Everybody looked at him and waited.

41:27.000 --> 41:38.000
Thomas Sawyer, where were you on the 17th of June at the hour of midnight?

41:39.000 --> 41:41.000
In the graveyard.

41:42.000 --> 41:44.000
Why?

41:45.000 --> 41:53.000
I went there to see ghosts with a dead cat.

41:56.000 --> 42:01.000
St. Petersburg laughed and the judge looked angry.

42:03.000 --> 42:08.000
And where were you in the graveyard, Thomas?

42:09.000 --> 42:14.000
Behind the trees near Haas-Williams grave.

42:15.000 --> 42:20.000
Engine Joe's face suddenly went white.

42:22.000 --> 42:29.000
Now, my boy, said the judge, tell us your story.

42:31.000 --> 42:35.000
And so Tom told his story.

42:36.000 --> 42:42.000
And St. Petersburg sat and listened to him with open mouths.

42:45.000 --> 42:48.000
And then Muff Potter fell.

42:49.000 --> 42:55.000
And engine Joe jumped with the knife and crash.

42:56.000 --> 43:03.000
Engine Joe jumped through the window and was out and away in a second.

43:06.000 --> 43:11.000
St. Petersburg loved Tom for a week.

43:12.000 --> 43:15.000
But Tom was not happy.

43:16.000 --> 43:19.000
Engine Joe was not in jail.

43:20.000 --> 43:23.000
And he was a dangerous man.

43:25.000 --> 43:28.000
Tom slept badly for weeks.

43:30.000 --> 43:34.000
The slow summer days went by.

43:35.000 --> 43:39.000
Engine Joe did not come back to St. Petersburg.

43:40.000 --> 43:43.000
And Tom began to forget.

43:48.000 --> 43:50.000
Chapter 4.

43:51.000 --> 43:53.000
Treasure.

43:55.000 --> 44:03.000
There is a time in every boy's life when he wants to go and dig for treasure.

44:04.000 --> 44:07.000
And that time came for Tom.

44:09.000 --> 44:14.000
So, one hot summer's day, he went to find Hock.

44:15.000 --> 44:18.000
Hock liked the idea of treasure.

44:19.000 --> 44:22.000
Where are we going to dig?

44:23.000 --> 44:24.000
He asked.

44:25.000 --> 44:28.000
An old dead tree is best.

44:29.000 --> 44:32.000
Who puts the treasure under old trees?

44:34.000 --> 44:35.000
Robbers!

44:36.000 --> 44:37.000
Said Tom.

44:38.000 --> 44:40.000
And then they go away.

44:41.000 --> 44:44.000
Or they forget to come back for the treasure.

44:46.000 --> 44:49.000
There's a dead tree on Cardiff Hill.

44:50.000 --> 44:51.000
Said Hock.

44:52.000 --> 44:53.000
Let's go there.

44:54.000 --> 44:57.000
I've got an old pick and shovel.

44:59.000 --> 45:02.000
It was three miles to the old tree.

45:03.000 --> 45:07.000
And the boys arrived tired and hot.

45:09.000 --> 45:12.000
They dug for an hour or two.

45:13.000 --> 45:15.000
But they didn't find any treasure.

45:17.000 --> 45:19.000
Then they stopped.

45:20.000 --> 45:24.000
And Tom looked down at an old house at the foot of the hill.

45:25.000 --> 45:27.000
Hey, look!

45:28.000 --> 45:29.000
He said.

45:30.000 --> 45:32.000
Nobody lives in that old house.

45:33.000 --> 45:35.000
Let's go there.

45:36.000 --> 45:40.000
Old houses are always good for treasure.

45:42.000 --> 45:44.000
Good for ghosts, too.

45:45.000 --> 45:46.000
Said Hock.

45:48.000 --> 45:51.000
They took the pick and shovel with them.

45:52.000 --> 45:57.000
Went down the hill and into the old house.

45:59.000 --> 46:02.000
They looked in all the rooms downstairs.

46:03.000 --> 46:05.000
And then went upstairs.

46:07.000 --> 46:11.000
But there was no treasure and no ghosts.

46:13.000 --> 46:15.000
Then they heard a noise.

46:16.000 --> 46:18.000
Said Tom suddenly.

46:19.000 --> 46:20.000
What's that?

46:22.000 --> 46:23.000
Ghosts?

46:25.000 --> 46:26.000
Whispered Hock.

46:29.000 --> 46:31.000
There were holes in the floor.

46:32.000 --> 46:36.000
And through them, the boys could see into the rooms downstairs.

46:38.000 --> 46:39.000
No.

46:40.000 --> 46:41.000
Tom whispered.

46:42.000 --> 46:43.000
Tom whispered.

46:44.000 --> 46:46.000
It's two men.

46:47.000 --> 46:49.000
One is the old Spaniard.

46:51.000 --> 46:54.000
He came to live in the village last week.

46:55.000 --> 46:57.000
I don't know the other man.

46:58.000 --> 46:59.000
Shh.

47:00.000 --> 47:01.000
Let's listen to them.

47:04.000 --> 47:07.000
The two men sat down on the floor.

47:08.000 --> 47:14.000
The Spaniard had a green hat and long white hair.

47:15.000 --> 47:19.000
The other men was small and dark.

47:21.000 --> 47:25.000
He took out a bag and began to open it.

47:27.000 --> 47:29.000
It's hot in here.

47:30.000 --> 47:31.000
The Spaniard said.

47:32.000 --> 47:34.000
He took off his green hat.

47:35.000 --> 47:40.000
And then he took off his long white hair.

47:42.000 --> 47:43.000
Tom!

47:44.000 --> 47:46.000
Hock whispered upstairs.

47:47.000 --> 47:50.000
That's engine Joe.

47:53.000 --> 47:59.000
We took $650 when we robbed that house.

48:01.000 --> 48:03.000
Said the second man.

48:05.000 --> 48:08.000
He took some money out of the bag.

48:10.000 --> 48:13.000
We can take $50 with us now.

48:15.000 --> 48:18.000
What are we going to do with the 600?

48:21.000 --> 48:23.000
Leave it here.

48:24.000 --> 48:25.000
Said engine Joe.

48:27.000 --> 48:31.000
We can come back and get it next week.

48:32.000 --> 48:33.000
Here.

48:34.000 --> 48:35.000
Give me the bag.

48:38.000 --> 48:41.000
He walked across the room to the fireplace.

48:42.000 --> 48:45.000
Moved two big stones from the floor.

48:47.000 --> 48:49.000
And began to dig with his knife.

48:51.000 --> 48:56.000
Upstairs, the two boys watched excitedly.

48:57.000 --> 48:58.000
Treasure.

48:59.000 --> 49:05.000
Six hundred dollars of wonderful treasure.

49:07.000 --> 49:09.000
Engine Joe stopped digging.

49:11.000 --> 49:12.000
Hello.

49:13.000 --> 49:14.000
What's this?

49:15.000 --> 49:16.000
He said.

49:17.000 --> 49:19.000
There's something here.

49:20.000 --> 49:22.000
It's an old box.

49:24.000 --> 49:27.000
The two men got the box out.

49:28.000 --> 49:29.000
And opened it.

49:32.000 --> 49:33.000
It's money.

49:34.000 --> 49:36.000
Said engine Joe's friend.

49:38.000 --> 49:41.000
Engine Joe put his hand into the box.

49:43.000 --> 49:47.000
There are thousands of dollars here.

49:48.000 --> 49:49.000
He said.

49:50.000 --> 49:55.000
And the two men looked at the money with happy smiles.

49:59.000 --> 50:03.000
But who began engine Joe's friend?

50:05.000 --> 50:06.000
Don't ask.

50:07.000 --> 50:08.000
Engine Joe said.

50:09.000 --> 50:11.000
It's our money now.

50:14.000 --> 50:17.000
We can't take it with us today.

50:18.000 --> 50:19.000
Said his friend.

50:20.000 --> 50:21.000
What can we do with it?

50:23.000 --> 50:24.000
Put it back under the floor?

50:25.000 --> 50:26.000
Yes.

50:27.000 --> 50:28.000
Said engine Joe.

50:31.000 --> 50:33.000
Happy faces upstairs.

50:35.000 --> 50:36.000
No.

50:38.000 --> 50:41.000
Very unhappy faces upstairs.

50:43.000 --> 50:45.000
Let's put it under the cross.

50:46.000 --> 50:48.000
Nobody goes there.

50:50.000 --> 50:52.000
We can take it there tonight.

50:53.000 --> 50:59.000
When night came, the two men carried all the money away.

51:00.000 --> 51:06.000
The boys did not go after them, because they were afraid of engine Joe.

51:07.000 --> 51:14.000
But they wanted very much to find that cross.

51:15.000 --> 51:19.000
For a week, the two men carried all the money away.

51:20.000 --> 51:26.000
For a week, the two boys thought and thought about the treasure.

51:28.000 --> 51:31.000
It was under the cross.

51:32.000 --> 51:35.000
But where was the cross?

51:38.000 --> 51:43.000
In St. Petersburg, the boys watched the Spaniard carefully.

51:44.000 --> 51:47.000
But they didn't see a cross.

51:48.000 --> 51:51.000
And they didn't find the treasure.

51:57.000 --> 51:59.000
Chapter 5.

52:00.000 --> 52:02.000
In the cave.

52:05.000 --> 52:09.000
The next Saturday was Becky Thatcher's birthday.

52:10.000 --> 52:14.000
And all Becky's friends were very excited.

52:15.000 --> 52:19.000
It's going to be a wonderful day.

52:20.000 --> 52:22.000
Becky told Tom.

52:23.000 --> 52:26.000
We're going to have a picnic by the river.

52:27.000 --> 52:32.000
And after that, we can visit McDougall's cave.

52:34.000 --> 52:43.000
So in the morning, a big boat took Becky, Tom, and all their friends down the river.

52:45.000 --> 52:48.000
There were some older children on the boat, too.

52:49.000 --> 52:53.000
But all the mothers and fathers stayed at home.

52:55.000 --> 52:57.000
Picnics are better without them.

53:00.000 --> 53:04.000
And it was a very happy, noisy picnic.

53:07.000 --> 53:11.000
After the picnic, the children took out their candles

53:12.000 --> 53:16.000
and ran up the hill to the cave.

53:18.000 --> 53:21.000
The mouth of the cave was dark.

53:22.000 --> 53:25.000
And some of the children were afraid at first.

53:26.000 --> 53:29.000
But caves are exciting.

53:30.000 --> 53:33.000
So in the end, everybody went in.

53:36.000 --> 53:40.000
McDougall's cave was very, very big.

53:41.000 --> 53:44.000
With hundreds of tunnels and rooms.

53:46.000 --> 53:52.000
The tunnels went up, down, and into the hill for miles.

53:54.000 --> 53:58.000
You could walk for days in McDougall's cave.

54:00.000 --> 54:02.000
Nobody knew all the cave.

54:04.000 --> 54:07.000
But many people knew the tunnels near the door.

54:08.000 --> 54:12.000
You could play all day in these tunnels.

54:14.000 --> 54:17.000
Tom, of course, knew them well.

54:20.000 --> 54:30.000
For hours, the children walked and ran through the cave, up and down the tunnels, in and out of the rooms.

54:31.000 --> 54:41.000
In the evening, they came out and walked down the hill to the boat, tired, but happy.

54:43.000 --> 54:48.000
When the boat arrived back in St. Petersburg, it was dark.

54:49.000 --> 54:55.000
Huck Finn saw the boat, but he did not know about the picnic.

54:56.000 --> 55:05.000
He did not go to birthday picnics, of course, because the mothers of St. Petersburg did not like him.

55:07.000 --> 55:14.000
But tonight, Huck was only interested in treasure, engine Joe's treasure.

55:16.000 --> 55:20.000
Engine Joe was in an old building by the river.

55:21.000 --> 55:25.000
And Huck waited in the street near the building.

55:27.000 --> 55:34.000
Perhaps, he thought, engine Joe's cross isn't there.

55:35.000 --> 55:37.000
And the box of money.

55:39.000 --> 55:42.000
I must wait and watch.

55:43.000 --> 55:46.000
I can tell Tom about it tomorrow.

55:51.000 --> 55:54.000
But engine Joe didn't come out.

55:55.000 --> 56:04.000
At midnight, it began to rain, and Huck waited all night in the cold street.

56:06.000 --> 56:12.000
In the morning, he could not move, and he could not speak.

56:13.000 --> 56:19.000
He felt cold, then hot, then cold.

56:20.000 --> 56:22.000
Then hot again.

56:23.000 --> 56:29.000
Mrs. Douglas, a woman from the church, found him in the street.

56:30.000 --> 56:35.000
She took him to her home and put him to bed.

56:36.000 --> 56:40.000
And there he stayed for two weeks.

56:42.000 --> 56:44.000
He was very ill.

56:45.000 --> 56:49.000
And so, he did not hear about Tom and Becky.

56:51.000 --> 56:58.000
But on Sunday morning, all St. Petersburg knew about Tom and Becky.

56:59.000 --> 57:04.000
Because they were not on the boat when he came back to the village.

57:06.000 --> 57:08.000
Where were they?

57:09.000 --> 57:11.000
Were they lost in the cave?

57:12.000 --> 57:14.000
And were they alive?

57:15.000 --> 57:16.000
Or dead?

57:21.000 --> 57:25.000
At first, Tom and Becky played with their friends in the cave.

57:27.000 --> 57:32.000
Then Tom wanted to go down a new tunnel, and Becky went with him.

57:34.000 --> 57:41.000
They walked and talked, and went into a second tunnel, then a third.

57:43.000 --> 57:47.000
Sometimes Tom put a mark with candle smoke on the tunnel wall.

57:48.000 --> 57:52.000
He wanted to find the mouth of the cave again.

57:54.000 --> 57:59.000
Then they came out of the tunnels into a big room.

58:00.000 --> 58:06.000
There were hundreds of bats in this room, and the candles woke them up.

58:07.000 --> 58:14.000
Tom took Becky's hand, and they ran into the nearest tunnel with the bats behind them.

58:15.000 --> 58:20.000
But one bat hit Becky's candle, and it went out.

58:21.000 --> 58:29.000
The children ran and ran through the tunnels, and at last, they got away from the bats.

58:30.000 --> 58:33.000
They stopped and sat down.

58:34.000 --> 58:39.000
Suddenly, it was very, very quiet.

58:40.000 --> 58:42.000
Where are we now, Tom?

58:43.000 --> 58:47.000
Becky whispered, afraid.

58:48.000 --> 58:51.000
I don't know, said Tom.

58:52.000 --> 58:59.000
I think it's time to go back, but we can't go through that big room because of the bats.

59:00.000 --> 59:02.000
Let's go down this tunnel.

59:03.000 --> 59:07.000
They went down one tunnel, then a second, a third, a fourth.

59:08.000 --> 59:12.000
Then they wanted to find the big room with the bats again.

59:13.000 --> 59:15.000
But they couldn't.

59:16.000 --> 59:18.000
Becky began to cry.

59:19.000 --> 59:23.000
Tom, we can't get out!

59:24.000 --> 59:26.000
We're lost, Tom!

59:27.000 --> 59:29.000
We're lost!

59:30.000 --> 59:33.000
They walked and walked.

59:34.000 --> 59:38.000
When they were tired, they sat down.

59:39.000 --> 59:43.000
Then they got up and walked again.

59:44.000 --> 59:48.000
Then they got up and walked again.

59:49.000 --> 59:51.000
Time went by.

59:52.000 --> 59:55.000
Was it day or night?

59:56.000 --> 59:58.000
They didn't know.

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:04.000
Then Tom wanted to find water.

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:11.000
They had nothing to eat, and they must have something to drink.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:16.000
They found a very small river, and sat down next to it.

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:24.000
Becky said, Tom, we must stay here, near this river.

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:32.000
This is our last candle, and he did not finish.

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:35.000
But Becky understood.

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:38.000
Tom?

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:41.000
Yes, Becky.

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:45.000
Are they going to come and look for us?

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:47.000
Of course!

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:51.000
When the boat gets to St. Petersburg,

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:54.000
we'll get to St. Petersburg.

01:00:55.000 --> 01:00:59.000
We'll get to St. Petersburg.

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:05.000
But how can they find us in these hundreds of tunnels?

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:07.000
Oh, Tom?

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:09.000
Tom?

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:14.000
We're going to die in here!

01:01:17.000 --> 01:01:20.000
Becky began to cry again.

01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:23.000
Then the candle went out,

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:27.000
and the two children were in the dark.

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:31.000
They sat for hours and hours.

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:40.000
They slept a little, then woke up, then slept again.

01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:46.000
Was it Sunday now or Monday?

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:50.000
Suddenly Tom sat up.

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:53.000
Listen!

01:01:57.000 --> 01:01:59.000
Somebody's calling!

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:05.000
The two children listened.

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:10.000
They heard it again, a little nearer.

01:02:11.000 --> 01:02:13.000
They called back.

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:18.000
Then they began to walk down the tunnel in the dark,

01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:21.000
with their hands on the wall.

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:25.000
They stopped and listened again.

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:29.000
But now they couldn't hear anything.

01:02:31.000 --> 01:02:35.000
Slowly, they went back to their river.

01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:43.000
They slept again and woke up very, very hungry.

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:49.000
Perhaps it's Tuesday now, Tom thought.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:52.000
What can I do?

01:02:53.000 --> 01:02:55.000
I must do something.

01:02:57.000 --> 01:02:59.000
Then he had an idea.

01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:04.000
Becky, listen.

01:03:05.000 --> 01:03:08.000
I've got a long string in my pocket.

01:03:09.000 --> 01:03:15.000
I can go down some of the small tunnels and get back to you with the string.

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:18.000
You wait here.

01:03:19.000 --> 01:03:28.000
Slowly and carefully, Tom went down the first tunnel on his hands and knees.

01:03:29.000 --> 01:03:35.000
Then the tunnel wall on his right finished, and there was nothing.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:40.000
Tom put out his hand to feel the floor.

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:47.000
And just then, away to his right, he saw a hand.

01:03:49.000 --> 01:03:52.000
A hand with a candle.

01:03:55.000 --> 01:03:58.000
At once, Tom called out.

01:03:59.000 --> 01:04:00.000
Help!

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:02.000
He cried.

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:10.000
The hand moved, and Tom saw an arm and a face.

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:14.000
It was engine Joe.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:21.000
Tom was very afraid, but engine Joe was afraid too.

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:26.000
And he quickly ran away down the tunnel.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:34.000
Tom went back to Becky, but he did not tell her about engine Joe.

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:38.000
Tom waited for an hour.

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:42.000
Then went into a different tunnel with his string.

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:47.000
Then a third tunnel.

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:55.000
It was Tuesday evening, and St. Petersburg waited.

01:04:56.000 --> 01:05:05.000
Many of the villagers were in the cave, and they looked for the children day and night.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:13.000
But they heard nothing, saw nothing, and found nothing.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:20.000
Then, late that evening, there was a sudden noise in the streets.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:25.000
People began to run to the Thatcher's house.

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:31.000
They're here! Becky and Tom are here!

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:38.000
Most of the village came to listen to Tom's story.

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:43.000
It was in the sixth tunnel, he told them.

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:51.000
I went to the end of my string, and suddenly, I could see daylight.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:55.000
There was a little hole in the cave wall.

01:05:56.000 --> 01:06:05.000
I put my head out, and there was the river, right under my nose.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:13.000
I went back and got Becky, and we climbed out through the hole.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:17.000
Then we stopped a boat on the river.

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:23.000
We were five miles from the mouth of the cave.

01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:39.000
Tom was very tired after his three days in the cave, and he went to bed and stayed there for two days.

01:06:41.000 --> 01:06:49.000
He heard about Hock, and went to see him on Sunday, and then every day.

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:54.000
But Mrs. Douglas was always in the room.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:07:00.000
You can just say hello, she told Tom.

01:07:01.000 --> 01:07:09.000
And then you must go. Hock is very ill, and he needs to sleep.

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:19.000
So Tom could not talk about anything exciting, and he could not tell Hock about engine Joe.

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:32.000
One day, about two weeks after the picnic, Tom was in Becky's house, and her father came in.

01:07:33.000 --> 01:07:44.000
Well, Tom, Mr. Thatcher said, would you like to go back to the cave again, one day?

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:51.000
I'm not afraid of that cave, said Tom.

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:54.000
Mr. Thatcher laughed.

01:07:55.000 --> 01:07:59.000
There are a lot of people like you, Tom.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:04.000
But nobody's going into that cave again.

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:14.000
There are big doors across the cave mouth now, and nobody can open them.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:19.000
Tom's face went white.

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:26.000
But Mr. Thatcher, engine Joe's in that cave.

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:33.000
An hour later, 50 men were at the cave, and they opened the doors.

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:47.000
Engine Joe was on the ground, dead, his face to the door, and his knife in his hand.

01:08:47.000 --> 01:08:54.000
Chapter 6

01:08:54.000 --> 01:09:01.000
Under the Cross

01:09:02.000 --> 01:09:08.000
The day after engine Joe's funeral, Hock was out of bed.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:14.000
He and Tom walked slowly out of the village.

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:27.000
They had a good long talk, and Hock heard all about the picnic, the cave, and engine Joe.

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:34.000
We're never going to find the money now, said Hock.

01:09:35.000 --> 01:09:38.000
Hock, said Tom.

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:42.000
The money isn't in St. Petersburg.

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:47.000
It's in the cave. I know it is.

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:52.000
Why was engine Joe in the cave?

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:59.000
Because he took the box of money there, right?

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:03.000
Hock looked excited.

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:08.000
Say that again, Tom.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:13.000
The money's in the cave.

01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:17.000
And we can get to it easily.

01:10:18.000 --> 01:10:20.000
Let's go there now.

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:25.000
I've got some candles and a long string.

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:31.000
We can take a boat and put it back later.

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:39.000
Twenty minutes later, the boys were in a boat on the Mississippi.

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:48.000
They went eight miles down the river, and then Tom stopped by some small trees.

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:51.000
Here we are!

01:10:52.000 --> 01:10:53.000
He said.

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:58.000
Tom's hole was just behind the trees.

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:03.000
Tom took a candle and climbed in.

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:07.000
Hock climbed in after him.

01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:15.000
Engine Joe never found this hole, said Tom.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:21.000
Or he did find it and couldn't get through it.

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:24.000
It's very small.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:31.000
The boys went carefully through the tunnels with their string.

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:35.000
Then Tom stopped.

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:40.000
I saw engine Joe about here.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:42.000
He said.

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:47.000
And look, Hock! There's the cross!

01:11:49.000 --> 01:11:53.000
There was a big smoke cross on the tunnel wall.

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:58.000
The boys looked up and down the tunnel.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:02.000
But there was no box of money.

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:10.000
Engine Joe said, under the cross, said Tom.

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:14.000
Perhaps it's under the ground.

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:19.000
Look, we can move these stones.

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:26.000
The boys took their knives and began to dig by the tunnel wall.

01:12:28.000 --> 01:12:34.000
Very soon, they found a second, smaller tunnel under the wall.

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:42.000
They climbed down into it and came into a small room.

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:54.000
There was a bed, two whiskey bottles, some old shoes, and the box of money.

01:13:01.000 --> 01:13:07.000
When somebody finds treasure, everybody hears about it very quickly.

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:13.000
The two boys carried the box through the village.

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:20.000
And when they got to Aunt Polly's house, half the village was with them.

01:13:21.000 --> 01:13:24.000
Everybody went into the house.

01:13:27.000 --> 01:13:29.000
Oh, Tom! Tom!

01:13:30.000 --> 01:13:32.000
Cried Aunt Polly.

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:35.000
What is it now?

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:40.000
And what half you got there?

01:13:42.000 --> 01:13:46.000
Tom put the box on the table and opened it.

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:53.000
There were $12,000 in that box.

01:13:56.000 --> 01:14:06.000
And suddenly, Tom Sawyer and Huckleberry Finn were the richest people in St. Petersburg.

